    "overall_strategy": "The prebiotic synthesis network for arginine is designed with convergent pathways focusing on ornithine as a central hub intermediate. Hydrothermal environments provide foundational C1-C3 units like formate and pyruvate through mineral-catalyzed reductions. Surface environments enable chain elongation and Strecker synthesis for ornithine via aminopropanal intermediates using cyanosulfidic chemistry. Biochemical assembly incorporates the guanidino group using cyanamide or guanidine donors. Multiple routes ensure redundancy: two primary paths to ornithine (hydrothermal via glutamate and surface via Strecker chain building) and two final steps (with cyanamide or guanidine). This creates interconnected flows across environments, with HCN and pyruvate as additional hubs. Ten distinct pathways are outlined, varying branch combinations for robustness under prebiotic variability.",
